<br>
&quot;Is there any chance of consideraing warriors' ability to hold aggro without having to rely on procs? As it stands, a paladin or a shadowknight can hold aggro much more efficiently and effectively, which is fine, but the difference between the AC and HPs of warriors and knights has gradually gotten smaller and smaller, making it harder for warriors to function in experience groups, and /defensive is just about our last class-defining ability, and I don't use defensive much in an experience group. Moreover, things like EB proc'ing weapons are not available to a lot of tanks.&quot;<br>
<br>
Scott's inital answer:<br>
<br>
&quot;Um... Yes.&quot;<br>
<br>
